                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "The autofly swarm strips the flesh from living creatures and breaks down the material into components it can use to create more autoflies. For every 2 damage dealt by an autofly swarm to living creatures in a single round, the autofly swarm regains 1 Hit Point.",
                "name": "Consume Flesh",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "The autofly swarm can also repair other constructs. Once per day as a full action, the autofly swarm can restore 1d8 Hit Points to any constructs or objects that share its space.",
                "name": "Rebuild",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "Like anacites, autoflies are solar-powered constructs, though they can function at reduced capacity away from light. In areas of darkness, the autofly swarm gains the staggered condition.",
